1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,400
(Pop quiz)
My name is

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:07,480
(This episode's highlights)
Yang Glory.

3
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:08,360
What's my name?

4
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,360
(In unison)
Ning Waver!

5
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:11,400
(Teacher Ning's pop quiz)
What's his name?

6
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:12,560
- Ding Pillar.
- Ding Pillar.

7
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,120
And you?

8
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:14,960
- Ke Stubborn.
- Ke Stubborn.

9
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,200
I think we should test him.

10
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,280
(After yours, it's your turn)
He came in later.

11
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:17,760
This one.

12
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:18,640
What about me?

13
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:20,160
Ding Pillar.

14
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:20,560
How about this?

15
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,680
(Lightbulb moment)
Let's each use our own name

16
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:22,120
and do one.

17
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:23,000
For example, I'm

18
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,600
Ning Waver.

19
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,080
I...

20
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,000
Ke Stubborn. I...

21
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:30,200
Jin Thrifty.

22
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:33,080
I'm Ding Pillar.

23
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:34,280
(Let me take a look)

24
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,320
Mine's easy.

25
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,120
Hmph, ha, hey!

26
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:39,500
(Fun on the road)
Girl, you sit at the bow.

27
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:41,640
(Immediately sings along)
I'll sit at the bow.

28
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:43,000
Put the light in front of you.

29
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,320
(I know how to get the shot)
Your face will look better.

30
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:45,200
Looking toward the light

31
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:45,920
gives it more vibe.

32
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:46,760
(Full-on vibe)
A silhouette shot.

33
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:47,760
It's so good.

34
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,420
(Fun)
Right?

35
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,360
Pull all of it out.

36
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:51,520
This feels so good.

37
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,200
(Super satisfying)
Try it.

38
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,200
Sometimes I watch those

39
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,840
(Loves watching)
pimple-popping videos.

40
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:55,280
So satisfying.

41
00:00:57,300 --> 00:01:00,380
=Truth Clubhouse=

42
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:02,340
(Truth Inn will fill you up,
but you have to hang in there)

43
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,200
It's scary today.

44
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:05,800
Seriously?

45
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:06,780
(Serious)
Seriously.

46
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:08,920
Did you know they said

47
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:10,800
today's filming location
has a mass grave?

48
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:11,940
(Frozen)

49
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:12,580
(Stumbles)

50
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:13,560
Good luck.

51
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,440
Which hand is hurt?

52
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,320
How are you going to protect me today?

53
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,120
How am I supposed to protect you?

54
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,640
You protect me.

55
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,520
(I can't hurt you)
How do I avoid accidentally hurting you?

56
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,540
(Still worried, asks again)
Does it hurt?

57
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:24,560
It's fine. It doesn't hurt.

58
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:25,880
Does it hurt if it's touched?

59
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,520
As long as I don't bend it.

60
00:01:27,620 --> 00:01:28,660
(Take care)

61
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:30,540
You're suspicious today.

62
00:01:30,540 --> 00:01:31,180
(Testing him)

63
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,080
Do you know why?

64
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,040
Why?

65
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,560
Of course I can't tell you now.

66
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:39,040
Then you might get ready for it.

67
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,680
(Getting into character)
When everyone gets here,

68
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,240
and once their cameras are rolling,

69
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,240
I'll make you look bad!

70
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:46,240
(Savage)
Fine.

71
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,960
Let's see

72
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:50,040
how you're gonna embarrass me.

73
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:50,700
(Grinning)

74
00:01:50,740 --> 00:01:53,260
(Chewing)

75
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,640
Your teeth will be pitch-black later.

76
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:56,360
Two are missing.

77
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:56,940
(Missing-teeth version)

78
00:01:57,060 --> 00:01:58,460
(My belly)

79
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:00,720
Get me a piece of chocolate.

80
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,200
The 100% one.

81
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,600
There are only a few 100% ones.

82
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,400
I only need one.

83
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,880
(Giving in for food)
Being the "killer" is too stressful.

84
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,440
And you had to write a character bio?

85
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,440
Yeah.

86
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,840
Okay, save one.

87
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,960
(Stashing snacks)
At my waist.

88
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,920
It's really scary here today, Ning.

89
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,000
Seriously?

90
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:16,440
No way.

91
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,480
(Certain)

92
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,600
Today definitely won't be scary.

93
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,160
Trust me.

94
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:20,760
Why do you say that?

95
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,180
(You're acting weird)

96
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,280
Don't test me like that.

97
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,600
I can't handle it right now.

98
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,120
(Ning comes clean)
One test and you'll expose me.

99
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,680
I can't lie right now.

100
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,360
(Jin sums it up)
You're stress-eating like crazy.

101
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:29,920
Yeah.

102
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,840
You crumble the second there's pressure.

103
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,360
Push me a little, and I chicken out.

104
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,080
That's why I really admired
Keyu that day.

105
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,020
(Just saying)

106
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,400
If it were me,
I'd have broken down long ago.

107
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,160
If it were me,

108
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,440
I'd be talking and crying.

109
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,600
(Sob sob)

110
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,320
It's not me!

111
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:47,240
(Serious)
Hearts Go with Tongcheng.

112
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,080
What does that mean?

113
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,000
Tongcheng Travel.

114
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,040
It's their ad.

115
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:52,260
(Made a fool of myself)

116
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,760
The speaker isn't great today.

117
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,600
This is the speaker? I thought it was...

118
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,520
The speaker's making that sound.

119
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:01,160
The speaker keeps making static today.

120
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,120
The speaker has static.

121
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,120
(Maxing out the creepy vibe)
Is it paranormal?

122
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,920
(Playing along)
Yeah, it's magnetic field interference.

123
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,600
It's fine. I brought crystals.

124
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,520
I brought my own crystals.

125
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,840
Crystals don't really do anything.

126
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,600
What would crystals even do?

127
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:19,960
They do.

128
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,560
(Firmly believes it works)
I'll switch this white one to my right.

129
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,440
Stop scaring me.

130
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,640
(So scared her voice is shaking)
Can you fix it?

131
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,520
The wire's bad.

132
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,280
The wire's not great.

133
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:29,920
I really can't handle this.

134
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,680
Fix it.

135
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,800
And Ding can't protect me today.

136
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,880
If Ding gets nervous
and grabs someone today,

137
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,420
(What do we do?)
his hand will hurt.

138
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,920
I told him yesterday

139
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,080
to be careful.

140
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:43,360
Today, he has to take care of himself.

141
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:43,840
We...

142
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:46,320
(Sensing it early)
We'll probably be panicking too.

143
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,400
Let me ask you.

144
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,560
Are you still scared?

145
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:50,120
(Brave Ning)
I'm actually not.

146
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:52,100
(Suspicious)

147
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,360
You don't feel anything now?

148
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:53,840
Well, not really.

149
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,720
I still feel a little.

150
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,520
But it's not like

151
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,880
(Getting braver)
I can't take it anymore.

152
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,080
Back in Season 1,

153
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,720
you'd kind of fall apart.

154
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,120
I feel like

155
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,160
your legs would go weak.

156
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,160
You'd even squat down and stuff.

157
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,040
Now you don't.

158
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,680
I'm scared of the sudden stuff.

159
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:09,420
(Shudders)

160
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,440
Stuff like that.

161
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:10,880
You know?

162
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:12,960
That's what scares me.

163
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,000
When it happens all at once.

164
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,120
Everyone's scared of that.

165
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,760
(Scared of sudden scares)
Everyone is.

166
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,600
It's like a balloon.

167
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,480
It suddenly pops.

168
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,640
(Jin keeps startling people)
Looks like I scare you a lot.

169
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,200
No.

170
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,400
You do that all the time.

171
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,080
I'm used to it.

172
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,880
Ding, protect yourself this time, okay?

173
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:30,920
(I'll take care of myself)
Okay.

174
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:31,640
Don't be scared.

175
00:04:32,820 --> 00:04:33,980
(Xin roars)

176
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,780
(Gets into character instantly)
Set, get ready.

177
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:38,980
(Cleaning carefully)

178
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,680
You're blowing it toward me?

179
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,860
(Shopkeeper, calm down)
Sorry, boss.

180
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,420
(Young Master Ke enters)

181
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:47,620
(Truth Inn Mini Theater, bonus edition)

182
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,000
And who might you be?

183
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,680
(Please)
Guest, please come in.

184
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,960
Eating or staying the night?

185
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,920
Ma'am, the usual.

186
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,760
(Afraid the guest will go hungry)
I already brought it out.

187
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:58,640
Let's do it again.

188
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,480
(Follow my lead)
I'll cue you.

189
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,880
Serve the food.

190
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,520
This is our house specialty.

191
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,560
Nine Yin Claws.

192
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,240
And some buns.

193
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,040
Enjoy, sir.

194
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:06,800
Thanks.

195
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,880
Shopkeeper,

196
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,760
is the Blade Gala here?

197
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,080
(We've been waiting for you)
You're here.

198
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,600
The time has come.

199
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,600
The Blade Gala begins now.

200
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,000
Follow me at once.

201
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,440
This way, please.

202
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,520
Find your own seats.

203
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:31,840
Sorry.

204
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,960
Everyone, I forgot
to say my name earlier.

205
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:36,240
I'm known as Ke Stubborn.

206
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,720
(Raises hand obediently)
Did I say my own name?

207
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:38,920
No.

208
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,400
I'll add mine too.

209
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,600
My name is

210
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,800
Yang Glory.

211
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,320
Yang Glory.

212
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:45,400
You're Ding...

213
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,560
Ding Pillar.

214
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,560
Ke Stubborn.

215
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,360
(Pop quiz)
What's my name?

216
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,160
(In unison)
Ning Waver!

217
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,200
(Teacher Ning's pop quiz)
What's his name?

218
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,360
- Ding Pillar.
- Ding Pillar.

219
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:54,920
And you?

220
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,720
- Ke Stubborn.
- Ke Stubborn.

221
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:57,880
What's her name?

222
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:58,760
- Yang Glory.
- Yang Glory.

223
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,760
Alright.

224
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,200
Who are you?

225
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,240
Jin Thrifty.

226
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,600
(You little brat)
You just said it.

227
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:05,420
(Slaps himself)

228
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,400
Okay.

229
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,380
(He Ha appears)
Wait.

230
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,520
I am the famous

231
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:13,600
fortune teller of the martial world.

232
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,520
(After some discussion)
Your name is Hehe Youming, right?

233
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,160
(Who are you thinking of?)
He Ha!

234
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:20,400
(Excuse me?)
Who are you calling Hehe Youming?

235
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:21,720
He Ha.

236
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,760
Okay, that's right.

237
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,500
(Ning has an idea)
Wait.

238
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,760
I think we should test him.

239
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,840
(After yours, it's your turn)
He came in later.

240
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,520
What's her name?

241
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,080
Yang Glory.

242
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:30,680
And this one?

243
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,120
No idea.

244
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:34,560
(You little brat)
Jin Thrifty.

245
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:35,760
Jin Thrifty.

246
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:36,920
And this one?

247
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,120
Ke Stubborn.

248
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,000
This one?

249
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,880
What about me?

250
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,400
Ding Pillar.

251
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,760
(As expected of the detective)
I know the four of you inside out.

252
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,800
Good.

253
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,480
Fine.

254
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:48,320
Then let this genius have a go.

255
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,160
(Pop quiz)
What's my name?

256
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,600
Your name is He Ha.

257
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,800
He Ha.

258
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,560
Players may head to the crime scene.

259
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,440
We're doomed.

260
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,440
(I know this part)
They're gonna scare us.

261
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,320
(This is bad)
Guys, we're cooked.

262
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,200
That means

263
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,800
there'll be some
physical activity there.

264
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,280
(Checking gear)
Let me tie my shoelaces first.

265
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:08,400
It's fine.

266
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,000
I'll walk like this.

267
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,360
(Holding on for life)
Or you can walk like this.

268
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,300
It's fine, Ding.

269
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,880
(Tables turned)
I'll protect you. I've got you.

270
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,560
Hurry. The lights are going off soon.

271
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:15,680
Wait!

272
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,660
(Mischievous brothers)
The lights are off!

273
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,480
Don't!

274
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,200
(Calm Ding is online)
You're all so childish.

275
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,800
Finally, we have this.

276
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,160
(Food mode activated)
I'm starving.

277
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,840
(Drawn by the sound)
I want a banana.

278
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,280
(The food expert is here)
This is gonna be so good.

279
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,040
Chicken feet.

280
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:35,060
(Young master hunting for food)
Give me a piece of bread.

281
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,160
Here, bread, Ning.

282
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,000
Is this konjac?

283
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,800
Thanks.

284
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,560
Spicy strips.

285
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,440
(Food enthusiast)
I ordered the spicy strips.

286
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,400
(Childish mode on)
I ordered them.

287
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,720
This is the one I wanted.

288
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,800
If anyone's scared,

289
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,100
(Ke is ready)
you can start looking for weapons now.

290
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:47,600
See?

291
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,120
Newbies always need stuff like that.

292
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,680
(Veteran advice)
Useless. Food is the most practical.

293
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,440
Really?

294
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,080
I didn't choose any food.

295
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:54,800
You have to pick food.

296
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,560
(Another veteran)
Grab as much as you can.

297
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:55,920
Yeah.

298
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,440
Only pick food.

299
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,000
(Yang wandered into expert town)
These are useless.

300
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,560
Totally useless.

301
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,360
Useless.

302
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:06,700
(Eating while packing)
Stop eating.

303
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,000
(Eating and taking)
Eat buns later if you're hungry.

304
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,000
Fine. Let's go.

305
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:11,880
Let's go to the meeting hall first.

306
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:14,680
Yeah, let's check out
the crime scene first.

307
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,080
Let's go.

308
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,120
Where's the meeting hall?

309
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:18,800
On the left.

310
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,000
To the left.

311
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,020
(Suddenly remembers something important)

312
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:24,460
(Can't let himself go hungry)

313
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:27,740
(Food supplies secured)

314
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:31,940
(Hungry boy catches up)

315
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:33,840
It's fine. It's not dark yet.

316
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,400
Once it's dark,

317
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,669
(Darkness hits Ding hard)
it'll be so scary.

318
00:08:35,669 --> 00:08:37,000
When it gets dark,

319
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,320
and the red lanterns come on...

320
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,240
When it gets dark,

321
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,280
(The image is already there)
everything's red. Red light everywhere.

322
00:08:42,059 --> 00:08:43,659
(Naughty Ding is on the move)

323
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,740
(What should I say now?)

324
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:46,600
Who's scaring people?

325
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,280
You are.

326
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:47,840
I'm not.

327
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,320
(It wasn't me anyway)
Who can get scared in broad daylight?

328
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,040
(I got scared)
You're already starting to scare people.

329
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,080
I'm dying.

330
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,760
This is bad.

331
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,320
(Getting bold now)
See that, "God"?

332
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,400
"God, " he's scaring people now.

333
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,280
Guys,

334
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,160
(Stirring the pot)
he asked for extra spice.

335
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,320
Don't do this to me.

336
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,360
Today, we'll give you

337
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,240
(You're actually pretty nice)
a solo task that doesn't need hands.

338
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:04,800
We're not at the meeting hall yet?

339
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:05,680
This...

340
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,520
I think I've really cleared my name.

341
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,560
(Eating all the way)
There's no way I'd carry him

342
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:09,600
this far.

343
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,560
I couldn't carry him either.

344
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,280
Okay, guys. We're here.

345
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,360
My...

346
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,320
My heart's already racing.

347
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,220
(A little panicked)

348
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:20,460
(Evidence search over)

349
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,960
Is my hair messy?

350
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,800
No.

351
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,560
Your butterfly glows at night.

352
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,400
That's awesome.

353
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,920
I noticed you keep changing perfumes.

354
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,620
(Sharp nose)

355
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,000
You're secretly sniffing me again.

356
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:32,140
(Dropped gear)

357
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:32,800
Who dropped something?

358
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,760
Mine, maybe.

359
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:36,120
Yours?

360
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,080
Once it's nighttime,

361
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,120
this will be scary.

362
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,080
How does it feel?

363
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:42,760
(Bad feeling)
Kind of doomed.

364
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:43,360
Looks okay to me.

365
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,360
It's okay.

366
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,440
Pretty calm.

367
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:45,880
Not bad.

368
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,120
No. You know why?

369
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:50,040
(As long as he hears us, we're here)
It's because he can hear our voices.

370
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,560
As long as we're with him, he's okay.

371
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:53,080
The scariest time was that one time.

372
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,160
The time with no sound.

373
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:55,800
No sound at all.

374
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,740
(That was real fear)
Five of us had to walk alone over there.

375
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:58,920
(Opening the inn door)

376
00:09:58,920 --> 00:09:59,320
Come on.

377
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,600
(Ke is finally back)
Finally home.

378
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,840
Now I know

379
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,360
(Sudden realization)
why we had to buy food.

380
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:09,300
(Fun behind-the-scenes code cracking)

381
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,000
Here.

382
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,040
This is it.

383
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,560
The tree with the red string.

384
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,880
Here. Three each.

385
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:14,440
Okay.

386
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:14,920
Here.

387
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:15,660
(Handing out incense)

388
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,720
Thanks for the incense, Ning.

389
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,800
Okay.

390
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:20,320
Here.

391
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,800
How do I light it? I don't know.

392
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,440
Use that fire stick.

393
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:25,600
(Step-by-step teaching)
Twist the top open like this.

394
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,080
Blow on it.

395
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:28,720
Yeah.

396
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,880
Don't you use this in period dramas?

397
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:33,560
Never have.

398
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:36,640
All the fire-lighting
in period dramas uses this.

399
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,080
I've never lit a fire in a period drama.

400
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,720
Does blowing really light it up?

401
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,840
Yeah. Just blow.

402
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:44,140
(Giving it a try)

403
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,080
No, Ding. Stop blowing.

404
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,600
Blow once, then light it like this.

405
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,360
This one's ready.

406
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,440
It's not hot enough yet.

407
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,400
Let it glow for a bit.

408
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,320
But you have to keep blowing on it.

409
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,480
Do you?

410
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,320
Yours isn't lit, Jin.

411
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,040
You gotta blow.

412
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,680
Ke, hold this for me.

413
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,080
What a whole ceremony.

414
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,440
That came out pretty naturally.

415
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,060
(Just realized it)

416
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,600
You really are his little
brother, right?

417
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,040
Yeah.

418
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:05,580
(Three months apart)

419
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,320
Little bro.

420
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,400
(Looking for modern tools)
Can we borrow a lighter?

421
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,680
Just close that thing.

422
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,280
Use a lighter.

423
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,020
(Not giving up)

424
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,760
He won't accept defeat.

425
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,160
Your brother won't accept defeat.

426
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,320
Look at him insisting on it.

427
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:24,420
(#Ding's fire-making struggle)

428
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,720
Where's the cap?

429
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,640
(Forced to stop)
Okay, I accept defeat. Seriously.

430
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,880
Don't burn your thumb.

431
00:11:30,580 --> 00:11:31,420
(Incense lit)

432
00:11:32,380 --> 00:11:33,220
(Incense lit +1)

433
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,240
(Sweet reminder)
Careful. Don't burn yourself.

434
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,240
(Scaring himself)
No one's coming out, right?

435
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:39,480
Probably not.

436
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,440
We bow three times, right?

437
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,000
Let's do it.

438
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:44,520
One by one.

439
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,800
Come on. Should we bow together?

440
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,360
Yeah.

441
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:48,840
(And there it is)
Sworn siblings.

442
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,800
Share joy and die together.

443
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,280
Okay, come on.

444
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,240
Share joy and die together.

445
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,880
That's a bad deal for you guys.

446
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,520
I'm older.

447
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,200
It's not really fair to you.

448
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,400
(Such a sweet talker)
We're willing to stay with you.

449
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,120
Share the good times.

450
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,200
Face the hard times together!

451
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:04,680
Come on.

452
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,160
First bow.

453
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,760
To heaven and earth.

454
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,360
(Something's off)
This isn't a wedding.

455
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,880
Second bow.

456
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,680
(But it doesn't matter)
To the parents.

457
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:15,080
Brothers and sister.

458
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,000
(Gotta cover both sides)
Bow to each other.

459
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:17,920
Okay.

460
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:18,800
Come on.

461
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,360
(#Wish delivery site)
May we solve this case.

462
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,480
Stay healthy.

463
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,080
May everything go well.

464
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:24,800
(Wish granted)

465
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,360
The light turned green.

466
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,080
A ghostly green glow.

467
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,640
(Improvised singing)
There's a beam of light.

468
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,700
(Mysterious code incoming)

469
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,120
Songsong Biscuit. I...

470
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,380
(I soar into the sky)

471
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,720
I'll remember this line.

472
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:42,940
(Translation needed ASAP)

473
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:46,700
(Loop memorization method)

474
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,440
Then I'll remember the next line.

475
00:12:53,860 --> 00:12:55,260
(Silent memorization method)

476
00:13:02,060 --> 00:13:03,340
(Emotional memorization method)

477
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:20,100
(#Everyone's crash course
in secret codes)

478
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,500
(Repeating it again and again)

479
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:25,080
Okay, who remembers it?

480
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,480
(I did, but it ran away)
I think it slipped out of my brain.

481
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,200
(Memory has left)
I already forgot.

482
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:32,220
(Songsong Biscuit. I...)

483
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:36,580
(You remembered it too)

484
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:38,700
(I soar into the sky)

485
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:41,260
(To greet my empty heart)

486
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,620
(Hahahahaha)

487
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,480
The two of us can just do the haha part.

488
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:48,140
(Immersive practice)

489
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,160
What does it mean?

490
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:50,920
No idea.

491
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,200
(That doesn't matter)
Don't worry about what it means.

492
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:54,300
(Translating by sound)
Welcome, Wanxiu. My heart, Konglong.

493
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:55,940
(Seven-second memory)
What was the first line again?

494
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:59,860
(Songsong Biscuit. I...)

495
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:07,340
(I soar into the sky)

496
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:10,340
(To greet my empty heart)

497
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:12,340
(Holding-it-together group)
Hahahahaha!

498
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,700
(Gen Z going feral)

499
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:17,500
(Possessed group)

500
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:18,840
No.

501
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,680
Tell us what's wrong.

502
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:24,840
(One little trick a day)
We have a Restore Card.

503
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,400
I have a card.

504
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,720
I have a Hint Card.

505
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,160
(Got everything covered)
An important clue Hint Card.

506
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,640
Not yet.

507
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:31,880
Leave that here for now.

508
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,880
I think we should rewind.

509
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,280
We pretty much remember it now.

510
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,160
Let's fix our own parts.

511
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,400
Let's run through it again.

512
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:37,800
Yeah.

513
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,360
Ning, remember the first line.

514
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:40,320
(Assigning tasks)
Jin, the second line.

515
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:40,920
I'll do the third.

516
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:41,680
You do the fourth.

517
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,400
Then...

518
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,520
No. Everyone memorizes
the fourth line more.

519
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,200
(Brain storage almost full)
My brain's not great.

520
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,400
We'll all remember the fourth line.

521
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:46,680
Okay.

522
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,160
No, I can only remember
the third line, Ding.

523
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,240
Mine's already hard enough.

524
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,440
You just remember the third line.

525
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,360
The three of us will do the fourth.

526
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:52,680
Okay.

527
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:54,600
My brain's not good.

528
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,480
(Same kind of people)
Mine isn't either.

529
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:57,040
Every single one

530
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,280
slipped right out of my head.

531
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,040
Say it.

532
00:14:59,340 --> 00:14:59,940
(What's wrong?)

533
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,800
You don't act like
an older brother at all.

534
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,080
I totally do.

535
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,040
(A confident big brother)
Young people have better brains.

536
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:04,800
Once you're old, you just...

537
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,680
I have a Hint Card.

538
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:09,120
An Item Card.

539
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,520
What's an Item Card?

540
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:11,840
A recorder?

541
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,000
I think we can remember it.

542
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,040
It might want us to restore

543
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,800
(Serious analysis)
that melody.

544
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,240
We have to sing it.

545
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,720
(New idea unlocked)
Did they add vocal runs to it?

546
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,680
It might be played backward.

547
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:22,800
Yeah.

548
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:23,920
Backward how?

549
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,080
Do you guys not go online?

550
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:25,840
It's just an online

551
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:26,640
meme.

552
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:27,520
Really?

553
