833
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,320
You stay seated.

834
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,640
That's so far.

835
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:02,520
Careful.

836
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:03,520
Okay.

837
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,000
Alright.

838
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,500
(Helping each other)

839
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:06,760
Let's go that way.

840
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,120
Okay.

841
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,360
Come help Jin.

842
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,200
I know.

843
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:09,880
Give it to me.

844
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:15,840
I'll hold him.

845
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:17,200
You take this.

846
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:17,760
Give it to me.

847
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:20,080
Hold this.

848
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:20,480
Okay.

849
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,360
Okay. Thanks.

850
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:25,000
Hmph, ha, hey.

851
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,420
(He hums one for everyone)

852
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,000
Let's go.

853
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:32,480
We've finally arrived
at the Ghost Market.

854
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:34,720
(Landed safely)
Why is the Ghost Market so loud?

855
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:36,200
Will people find out

856
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,600
we're not from the Ghost Market?

857
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:40,200
(Don't forget our identities)
We're all martial arts masters.

858
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:40,720
Right.

859
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:42,120
Fear comes from

860
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:43,240
(Masters with unknown skills)
bad skills

861
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,240
and not enough firepower.

862
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:45,880
(Backing down first)
Right?

863
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,160
So there's nothing to be afraid of.

864
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:48,380
(The lights went out)

865
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,080
I see something ahead.

866
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:49,840
What's that?

867
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:50,720
There's someone ahead.

868
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,880
Did he turn it off on us?

869
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:54,820
You even turned it off remotely?

870
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:55,920
(He's got a trick)
I turned it back on remotely.

871
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,240
They wouldn't let me use the light.

872
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,360
So I shut it off through Bluetooth.

873
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:00,080
Wait. What is this?

874
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,920
What does this mean?

875
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,280
It suddenly talked in my ear.

876
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,280
What is this thing?

877
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,120
It scared me to death.

878
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:09,680
Was it me?

879
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:11,540
(Slow to realize)

880
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:13,160
That scared me stiff.

881
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:15,480
What is that?

882
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,000
Join them.

883
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,320
(If you can't beat them, join them)
What's there to be scared of?

884
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:21,960
Hurry. Together.

885
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,960
Please sit.

886
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:28,500
(I've been waiting for you here)

887
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,920
(Sharp-eyed He)
Aren't you from the "scam company"?

888
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,440
Aren't you from the "scam company"?

889
00:24:32,660 --> 00:24:33,620
(Yes, I'm back again)

890
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:34,600
No way.

891
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:36,200
It's him!

892
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:36,840
From the "scam company".

893
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,800
I don't know what you're talking about.

894
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:39,720
It's him.

895
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,320
(Still fresh in Xin's memory)
I remember that voice.

896
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,520
The one who yelled at you last time.

897
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,680
The new leader.

898
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:42,960
Yeah.

899
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,160
Yeah.

900
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:44,560
Sit.

901
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:45,360
Get on.

902
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,200
They're probably gonna carry us later.

903
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:47,640
Probably.

904
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:48,680
No way. That's exhausting.

905
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,680
Let's go, "scammer".

906
00:24:50,460 --> 00:24:51,820
(Hey-ya)

907
00:24:51,820 --> 00:24:52,340
(Whoa-yo)

908
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:05,140
(It's actually got rhythm)

909
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:13,120
The ritual is complete.

910
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:15,120
Hit the road.

911
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:18,120
(Evil dragon roar)
Don't say that!

912
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:19,600
We're crooked.

913
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,360
(Coach He is here)
Turn a little right.

914
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:22,880
Come back.

915
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,800
We're turning left.

916
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:26,200
There's a tower too.

917
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,200
(Horror mode fully on)
Bro.

918
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,320
Don't do this.

919
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,640
I remember we had one before.

920
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,720
At the end of Season 3.

921
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:33,520
Yeah.

922
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,440
That really tall one.

923
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,000
Yeah.

924
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,760
He Yiwei?

925
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:37,600
He Yiwei.

926
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:38,600
(Who's cueing me?)
Why'd you call me?

927
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,320
That was his name last season.

928
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:42,840
(That's me)
I'm He Yiwei.

929
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:45,400
We're in the ditch.

930
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:46,480
Right!

931
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,840
A little right.

932
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:49,200
I bet when we gave the crew

933
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,880
our weights, we all lied.

934
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,720
Mine was real.

935
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:53,200
Mine too.

936
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:54,400
I've lost weight these days.

937
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:56,120
(Cards on the table)
Fine. I got heavier.

938
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:56,880
I admit it.

939
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:57,680
From eating in France.

940
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,360
Go right!

941
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,360
Why don't you let Jiawei drive?

942
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,400
(AAA Pro driving coach)
Jiawei's a go-kart pro?

943
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:03,880
Yeah.

944
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,840
This is what they call
a frog crashing into a pit.

945
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,280
I feel like these driving skills

946
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:09,720
can rival yours.

947
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,240
My driving's insanely good.

948
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:12,320
Do you even have a license?

949
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,740
Ke,

950
00:26:13,740 --> 00:26:14,800
(Pro driver)
I'm a pro.

951
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:15,480
Stop messing around.

952
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:17,360
I've been driving
for three or four years.

953
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,140
(Jin is curious)
What's that?

954
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:21,760
My little stress-relief toy.

955
00:26:21,760 --> 00:26:23,480
I thought it was key evidence.

956
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:25,240
What's that?

957
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,200
Her toy.

958
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:26,760
(Let me see)
For stress relief.

959
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:27,760
You just pull out the whiskers.

960
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:29,320
Does it trigger your trypophobia?

961
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:30,560
It's so good.

962
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,540
(Fun)
Right?

963
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,160
Pull them all out.

964
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:34,320
(Super satisfying)
This feels so good.

965
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,000
Try it.

966
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:35,760
What?

967
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,120
Sometimes I watch those

968
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,760
(Loves watching)
pimple-popping videos.

969
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:39,200
So satisfying.

970
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,000
I like watching those too.

971
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:40,880
One squeeze leaves a hole.

972
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:41,240
Blackheads.

973
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:41,980
(So satisfying)

974
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:43,280
We're here.

975
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:46,340
(Ghost Market half-day tour,
getting something for nothing)

976
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,080
Lucky Draw Stall!

977
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,080
Try your luck!

978
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,280
Come on! Open it!

979
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:52,520
Okay.

980
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:52,880
Come on!

981
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:53,400
Open.

982
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,960
(Watching)
Come on. Three, two, one.

983
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,320
Boss, this is too easy!

984
00:26:59,320 --> 00:26:59,800
What's easy?

985
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:00,960
(We like easy)
What do you mean?

986
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:01,360
Sir.

987
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:02,280
How do you play, bro?

988
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:04,960
Come on, guests. Join in!

989
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,280
(Luck)
We want to watch you play first.

990
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:07,000
We want to...

991
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:07,680
It's very simple.

992
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,560
There are different bamboo sticks here.

993
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:10,520
Mahjong?

994
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,160
No.

995
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:11,520
Pai gow.

996
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,600
One ghost coin

997
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,960
gets you one stick.

998
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,240
If the one you draw

999
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:17,280
(One coin, one draw. Match number)
matches mine,

1000
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,520
(You win the prize)
you'll get one ghost coin

1001
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:20,640
and one stamp.

1002
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,000
Eight, nine.

1003
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,000
Nine numbers, right?

1004
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,240
You can pick whatever you like.

1005
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:28,800
The odds aren't great either.

1006
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,440
How about this?

1007
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:30,440
(Free)
Boss, can we play for free?

1008
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,360
(Accidentally said it out loud)
No. Can we try it first?

1009
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:33,160
(Good at business)
Sure.

1010
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:33,760
Come on.

1011
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:35,520
I'll draw one.

1012
00:27:36,460 --> 00:27:38,140
(Random pick)

1013
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:39,720
Okay.

1014
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:43,020
(One out of nine. How do you win?)

1015
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:44,820
(Four, seven)

1016
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,000
You can't win this game.

1017
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,200
This is super easy.

1018
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,040
I won all this.

1019
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:51,560
Just tell us.

1020
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:52,360
Bro,

1021
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,800
(Begging to team up and rank up)
teach us how to play.

1022
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:54,960
Come on. You try one.

1023
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:55,840
Play a round.

1024
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:56,620
(Time to show you something)
Play a round.

1025
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:57,920
No one here

1026
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,240
can win every bet against me.

1027
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,480
No one here

1028
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,600
can win every bet against me.

1029
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:04,060
(The boss draws first)

1030
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:11,320
Let me see.

1031
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:12,240
(Peeking)

1032
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:12,680
Done drawing.

1033
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,500
(Saw everything)

1034
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:16,400
Come on.

1035
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:18,160
Three, two, one.

1036
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,400
Open!

1037
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:20,560
(Eight)

1038
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:21,280
Give me one.

1039
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,400
I get it.

1040
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:26,240
I get it.

1041
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:26,800
I know now.

1042
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,660
(The shock boys are synced again)
I get it too.

1043
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:30,960
How did you figure it out?

1044
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:34,080
It's counting the horses.

1045
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,120
How many horses there are.

1046
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,160
Yeah, how many horses.

1047
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,360
Is that it?

1048
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:38,960
I don't know.

1049
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,360
But it's probably that kind of game.

1050
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,040
I'm guessing.

1051
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:44,800
One first.

1052
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:45,160
No.

1053
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:45,600
Lend me one.

1054
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,360
He wants a fan (fan).

1055
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:50,120
(Needs a closer look)
One more round.

1056
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:51,440
Yeah. Play another round.

1057
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,240
Thank you.

1058
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:52,980
(Let us study this)

1059
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,940
(Demo version 2.0)
Let's keep playing.

1060
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,160
Wait.

1061
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:56,800
Hold on.

1062
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,120
If you're that sure you'll win,

1063
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:59,160
(Helpful)
why not go all in?

1064
00:28:59,160 --> 00:28:59,600
Bro.

1065
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:00,440
(No need)
Not all in.

1066
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:01,760
Go all in against him.

1067
00:29:01,760 --> 00:29:02,360
No.

1068
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:03,560
(R2 conservative investor)
What if I lose?

1069
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:04,560
Go all in.

1070
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:05,560
I've been winning all day.

1071
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:06,560
It wasn't easy.

1072
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,720
It's confirmed.

1073
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,160
Watch how they compare.

1074
00:29:09,540 --> 00:29:11,540
(Staring)

1075
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:14,600
Come on.

1076
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:17,560
Come on.

1077
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:18,680
Done betting?

1078
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,120
Done.

1079
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:27,320
Three, two, one.

1080
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:27,520
Open!

1081
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:28,460
(Seven)

1082
00:29:28,980 --> 00:29:29,580
(Seven)

1083
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:38,200
No one here can win
every bet against me.

1084
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:41,780
(Eight)

1085
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:42,920
Come on.

1086
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:43,800
Done betting?

1087
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:44,440
Done.

1088
00:29:44,940 --> 00:29:46,700
(Seven)

1089
00:29:46,820 --> 00:29:49,340
(Eight, seven)

1090
00:29:49,400 --> 00:29:50,000
Pay attention.

1091
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,120
Watch where his fan is.

1092
00:29:51,180 --> 00:29:52,440
(Figured it out)

1093
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,600
Smart.

1094
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:56,360
I'm just running a small business!

1095
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,080
This...

1096
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,120
You play a round.

1097
00:29:59,360 --> 00:29:59,840
Come on.

1098
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:00,520
You play one.

1099
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:01,240
Ding, play one.

1100
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,120
You guys are out of ghost coins.

1101
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:05,740
(That's a problem)

1102
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:07,680
Then I'll bet my life.

1103
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:09,200
(Such big trust)
No!

1104
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,200
You can't bet your life. Okay.

1105
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:13,800
Have you ever seen

1106
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:15,560
such a pretty woman in the Ghost Market?

1107
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,760
Just for that

1108
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,120
(On credit)
okay.

1109
00:30:22,340 --> 00:30:23,000
(Bro is generous)

1110
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:23,480
Okay.

1111
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:24,840
You've got good taste.

1112
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:27,840
Being good-looking
can pay the bills, right?

1113
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:28,440
Of course.

1114
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:29,400
- Yes!
- Right!

1115
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:30,520
In that case,

1116
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:31,520
let's do one more round.

1117
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,400
Okay.

1118
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:33,320
Come on.

1119
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:35,040
Play.

1120
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:37,180
(Official bet)

1121
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:44,620
(Boss draws)

1122
00:30:50,740 --> 00:30:52,740
(Placed by the shoulder)

1123
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:56,740
(Choosing)

1124
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:58,740
(Is Ding's guess right?)

1125
00:30:58,800 --> 00:30:59,920
Done.

1126
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:03,200
Three, two, one.

1127
00:31:03,260 --> 00:31:05,140
(Three)

1128
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:06,120
(Three)

1129
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:07,840
Smart!

1130
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:16,240
One.

1131
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:16,520
Two.

1132
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:17,840
This one's yours.

1133
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,240
(Borrowed and returned)
I'm paying one back, right?

1134
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:19,480
Okay.

1135
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:20,400
Well?

1136
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:21,720
We gotta keep going.

1137
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:23,720
Let's clean out his whole stall.

1138
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:26,880
I know. It's a 3x3 grid.

1139
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:27,360
Right.

1140
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:30,180
(Truth revealed)

1141
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:33,680
Here we go.

1142
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:34,200
Then...

1143
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:39,240
(Signaling)
Come on, dear guests.

1144
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:40,360
Six.

1145
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:42,080
This is three.

1146
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:44,280
Six, or...

1147
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:47,680
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine.

1148
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:48,960
Three.

1149
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,000
That tickles.

1150
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,440
Congratulations.

1151
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:54,440
(Prize)
Here. A stamp for you all.

1152
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:57,720
May the money roll in. Thanks.

1153
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:59,120
(A gentleman loves money. Take it)

1154
00:31:59,120 --> 00:31:59,760
Okay.

1155
00:31:59,760 --> 00:31:59,960
Go.

1156
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,160
(Triple luck)
Come take a look!

1157
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,400
Hi.

1158
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:10,200
Triple luck set.
You're guaranteed a great time!

1159
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,600
How does this work, boss?

1160
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:14,480
(Triple luck game rules)
All you need is one ghost coin.

1161
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:17,080
Then you get three chances
to shake the bell.

1162
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,960
(Try first, decide later)
We're broke. We wanna try it first.

1163
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,400
Then let's do one trial round.

1164
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:22,800
Okay.

1165
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:25,960
Each time you shake it,
we'll each take out one item.

1166
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:28,560
After all three shakes,

1167
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:31,320
if the items in our hands match,

1168
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:32,520
then you win.

1169
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,840
Okay. Come on. Let's try.

1170
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:43,640
This is way too hard.

1171
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:44,840
What does that mean?

1172
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:47,800
You're doing all this stuff here

1173
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,140
(Can't fool me)
to scam us.

1174
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:52,480
We're running an honest business.

1175
00:32:52,480 --> 00:32:54,320
We never scam anyone.

1176
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:56,280
Tell me how many things are under there.

1177
00:32:58,320 --> 00:32:59,200
Inside this...

1178
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:00,000
Let's go look.

1179
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:04,040
(Shop rules)
Our shop's back room

1180
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:06,280
isn't open for casual visits.

1181
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:08,320
What if I do visit?

1182
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:09,760
If you visit,

1183
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:11,520
we might get

1184
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:13,120
kicked out of the Ghost Market.

1185
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:14,080
(You may have a point)
What's that got to do with me?

1186
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:14,600
Right.

1187
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:15,920
I just need to get

1188
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:16,800
(But I'm not listening)
that stamp.

1189
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:19,000
(Ke's savage take)
Why do you all sound like robbers?

1190
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:20,800
I think he's the scammer.

1191
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:22,120
(Pure deception)
It's not triple luck.

1192
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,120
It's triple scam.

1193
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:23,660
(Ning sums it up)

1194
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:24,680
We're leaving.

1195
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:25,200
We're not playing.

1196
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,560
What's fun about this?

1197
00:33:26,560 --> 00:33:28,720
You all just said you're leaving, right?

1198
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:30,040
Give me back my coin.

1199
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:31,920
I gave you one coin earlier.

1200
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,400
That was a trial round.

1201
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:33,840
No.

1202
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:35,520
(Turning the tables)
We clearly gave you the coin.

1203
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:38,160
Now you guys sound like the scammers.

1204
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:39,160
No.

1205
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:40,200
We just tried it.

1206
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,920
See? We said it was a trial.

1207
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,800
Exactly.

1208
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:43,320
No need.

1209
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:44,560
It's just one or two coins.

1210
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:44,880
Not worth it.

1211
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:45,880
I believe...

1212
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,920
(Boss Jin speaking)
I'm a businesswoman too.

1213
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:49,040
Tell us how this game

1214
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:49,800
actually works.

1215
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:51,600
Give us a little hint,

1216
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,120
(You know)
right?

1217
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:53,640
For that little hint,

1218
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:56,200
we really do need ghost coins

1219
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,000
(No ghost coins, no game)
before you can play.

1220
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:57,760
How about this?

1221
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,360
(Ning has a plan)
Can we try one more round?

1222
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,520
Okay. One more trial round.

1223
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:01,600
Is that okay, boss?

1224
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:02,540
(Agrees right away)
Sure.

1225
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:04,120
Then you do it.

1226
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,640
Get ready.

1227
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:06,440
Spin.

1228
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:09,920
That's a win.

1229
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,460
(Ning the smooth talker)

1230
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:12,190
Two matching is enough, right?

1231
00:34:12,190 --> 00:34:14,040
(Follow the rules)
Only three matching counts.

1232
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,880
Three matching?

1233
00:34:15,880 --> 00:34:16,840
(They all start bluffing)
Exactly the same.

1234
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,000
That's three matching.

1235
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:19,400
(I don't trust you)
Then I need to ask.

1236
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:21,520
My human puppet,

1237
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:22,880
what are you holding

1238
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:24,120
over there?

1239
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:24,880
A tomato.

1240
00:34:25,060 --> 00:34:25,800
(See?)

1241
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,000
And you?

1242
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,260
A cantaloupe.

1243
00:34:28,260 --> 00:34:29,020
(See?)
See?

1244
00:34:29,020 --> 00:34:30,280
What we're holding is (different).

1245
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:31,670
This is too hard.

1246
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:33,120
It really is triple luck.

1247
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:33,920
It's all luck.

1248
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:36,120
Okay, boss. Play by yourself for now.

1249
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:36,800
We'll think about it.

1250
00:34:37,139 --> 00:34:38,219
(You're really not stopping us?)

1251
00:34:45,139 --> 00:34:46,699
(Coming back in defeat)

1252
00:34:48,630 --> 00:34:50,040
I got it. Here's the pattern.

1253
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:50,940
(Linghe's onto something)

1254
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,190
What's this?

1255
00:34:56,190 --> 00:34:57,120
You keep pointing like this.

1256
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,040
(Jin's a little confused)
What does it mean?

1257
00:34:58,040 --> 00:35:00,520
It's the number of shakes, right?

1258
00:35:00,520 --> 00:35:01,800
This one needs four shakes.

1259
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:02,760
This one is...

1260
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:05,160
Also four shakes.

1261
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:07,200
Then let's pay once.

1262
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:08,880
(Still need to test it)
Let's watch it one more time, okay?

1263
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,400
We can do it for free.

1264
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,600
(Free is better, right?)
Why pay?

1265
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:12,360
Come on.

1266
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:12,560
It's fine.

1267
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:14,260
(Renamed Ghost Market Bank)
We've got unlimited money now.

1268
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:15,160
(We're rich now)

1269
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,360
That place is the bank now.

1270
00:35:16,450 --> 00:35:17,400
It's a money tree.

1271
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,920
(Ke has an idea)
How about this, Ning?

1272
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,400
I'll keep winning money over there.

1273
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,200
Then I'll bring it to everyone.

1274
00:35:22,200 --> 00:35:24,040
You guys can play over here.

1275
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:24,480
Okay.

1276
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:26,320
(Ning calls it out)
You're fleecing one sheep dry.

1277
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,360
They're the sucker, huh?

1278
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,320
Exactly.

1279
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:29,320
Assembly line.

1280
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:29,720
Right?

1281
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:30,540
How about this?

1282
00:35:30,540 --> 00:35:31,920
(Trying a new way)
I'll ring the bell.

1283
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:33,960
You guys spin.

1284
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:35,120
Sure.

1285
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:35,440
Come on.

1286
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:43,480
These fruits really are

1287
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,400
(Pretty much spelling it out)
big and green.

1288
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:49,640
(Jin gets it)
So is it the cantaloupe or tomato?

1289
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:50,720
Okay.

1290
00:35:50,720 --> 00:35:52,600
You probably saw the fruits below.

1291
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,160
Let's play a simple game.

1292
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:55,840
I'll ring the bell once.

1293
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,280
The three of you need to strike

1294
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,480
a cute pose at the same time.

1295
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:02,080
(Ready to go)
If your poses match,

1296
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,440
then you win.

1297
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:07,140
(Off-screen hint)

1298
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:08,400
I think you're cute.

1299
00:36:09,580 --> 00:36:10,500
(Got it?)

1300
00:36:11,780 --> 00:36:12,740
(Lost)

1301
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:14,720
Three, two, one.

1302
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,400
(Sadly out)
Nope. Not the same.

1303
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,160
What a shame.

1304
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:23,440
What happened?

1305
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,000
One more.

1306
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,920
We have other expressions too.

1307
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:28,520
Okay.

1308
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,280
Then at the same time,

1309
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,680
show the same number.

1310
00:36:32,300 --> 00:36:33,060
(So clever)

1311
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:34,240
Okay.

1312
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:36,160
From one to ten, right?

1313
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:36,840
(Chaoyue's super obvious hint)
Come on.

1314
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:37,240
Three.

1315
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:38,640
What's going on?

1316
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,620
(Busted)

1317
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:40,920
Let's not hurt

1318
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,440
our shop's honest reputation.

1319
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,140
(Bold even when wrong)
No.

1320
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:45,080
No cheating.

1321
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:45,200
Come on.

1322
00:36:45,540 --> 00:36:46,600
(Yay)

1323
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:47,160
Show a number.

1324
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:48,080
Three, two, one. Start.

1325
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:52,720
(Ke's happy)
Look at that chemistry.

1326
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:54,560
We've had it since we were kids,

1327
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:55,000
right?

1328
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,200
Is it the same?

1329
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:57,200
Of course.

1330
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,480
But

1331
00:36:58,480 --> 00:36:59,560
the hands are different.

1332
00:37:00,240 --> 00:37:02,120
You have to use the same hand too.

1333
00:37:02,180 --> 00:37:02,500
(Happy)

1334
00:37:02,580 --> 00:37:04,540
(Not happy)

1335
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,320
Wait. I don't have arms.

1336
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:07,280
No hands.

1337
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:07,680
This...

1338
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:08,520
That's cheating.

1339
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:10,560
(Linghe doesn't get it)
You just said the exact same number.

1340
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,800
The exact same number.

1341
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,360
But it has to be the same hand too.

1342
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:14,680
(Let's break this down)
Let's call it like it is.

1343
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:15,640
You really did say

1344
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,720
the same number.

1345
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:18,120
(Come judge this)
"God, " he's cheating.

1346
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,200
Then we're even now.

1347
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,560
Let's do it again.

1348
00:37:21,560 --> 00:37:22,080
This time,

1349
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:23,280
still

1350
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:25,240
the same hand.

1351
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,800
and the same number.

1352
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:27,640
And a cute

1353
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:28,800
matching cute pose.

1354
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:29,840
Okay.

1355
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,280
Come on.

1356
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,800
Three, two, one. Start.

1357
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:33,820
(Exactly the same)

1358
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:35,440
Look at that.

1359
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:36,680
That really is...

1360
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:37,960
(Finally matched)
The same.

1361
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:38,680
This time.

1362
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:39,280
Right?

1363
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,360
What's your excuse now?

1364
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:41,320
It is the same.

1365
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,560
Alright then.

1366
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:43,880
Go ahead, everyone.

1367
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,960
Can we get the stamp now?

1368
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,800
Looks like you really do have chemistry.

1369
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,280
Then we'll...

1370
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,120
Here.

1371
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,000
Give you a stamp.

1372
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:51,440
Okay.

1373
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:51,760
Come on.

1374
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:55,380
(Stamp secured)

1375
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,120
Here to withdraw money.

1376
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:58,360
(Out of money)
Here to withdraw from me again?

1377
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,480
Here to withdraw money.

1378
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:00,400
This is a Lucky Draw Stall.

1379
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,200
(The boss is out of moves)
Not a cash withdrawal stall.

1380
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:02,720
Here.

1381
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,000
You guys make this so easy.

1382
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:05,840
Okay.

1383
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:06,480
Come on.

1384
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:06,760
Okay.

1385
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,120
How about...

1386
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:09,880
Boss.

1387
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,000
How about you just draw?

1388
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,850
(Too funny)
Or I'll just give it to you.

1389
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,400
Am I even needed here?

1390
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:15,520
Just pretend you don't know him.

1391
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:16,040
(Just pretend you don't)
Just pretend you don't know him.

1392
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:18,160
Is that six or three?

1393
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:19,480
Make it more obvious.

1394
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:20,520
It's three. That's clearly three.

1395
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:21,600
Okay.

1396
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,200
Here.

1397
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:25,360
Take it.

1398
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,160
Alright.

1399
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:27,640
Congrats.

1400
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:28,920
Thanks, boss.

1401
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,280
Congrats.

1402
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:32,000
(Come back when you're broke)
You should stock up over there.

1403
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:32,560
You'll run out soon.

1404
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:33,560
You might not be able to...

1405
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:34,640
It's straight-up robbery.

1406
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:35,920
Thanks.

1407
00:38:36,740 --> 00:38:37,760
(After taking a bite of bun)
Dear customers,

1408
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:40,000
come take a look.
We've got every weapon here.

1409
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,720
We've got Qide Swords
and Longdong Spears,

1410
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:42,320
dear customers.

1411
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,680
Qide Swords and Longdong Spears?

1412
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,200
(You don't know me?)
Do you know what I do?

1413
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:47,200
You are...

1414
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,160
I'm the one who makes Qide Swords.

1415
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,520
(Yeah, right)
Some knockoffs.

1416
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,120
Everything here is genuine.

1417
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:53,340
(Respect copyright)
Respect copyright.

1418
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:55,600
Give me two of those Qide Swords.

1419
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:56,120
Hello,

1420
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:58,160
this Qide Sword is one hundred thousand.

1421
00:38:58,160 --> 00:38:59,760
This Longdong Spear
is two hundred thousand ghost coins.

1422
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:00,800
One hundred thousand ghost coins, right?

1423
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:01,360
That's right.

1424
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,000
(More expensive than mine)
Why don't you buy the whole street?

1425
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,560
Our weapons are all genuine.

1426
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:05,320
That's the price, sir.

1427
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:08,400
Like I'd believe you.

1428
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:10,500
(Too many Skill Cards to choose from)

1429
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:14,640
Let's just leave first.

1430
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,480
What'll happen if we go first?

1431
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:17,580
(No way through)

1432
00:39:17,700 --> 00:39:18,900
(Calm and collected)

1433
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:21,160
Okay, then what if I do this?

1434
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:24,500
(That works too?)

1435
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:25,840
Get out!

1436
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:27,600
Black Tower grounds.

1437
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:27,920
No.

1438
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,720
No trespassing!

1439
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:30,200
Their line of sight is so high.

1440
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:32,080
(Raising a question)
Can we crawl in close to the ground?

1441
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,720
Can we crawl in close to the ground?

1442
00:39:33,720 --> 00:39:34,360
Close to the ground.

1443
00:39:36,940 --> 00:39:38,700
(Testing it out)

1444
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,660
(Tiny confidence)
We're the Eagle King's grandsons.

1445
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,240
Who's being the grandson?

1446
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:47,800
(Ning refuses)
You wanna be the grandson? You go ahead.

1447
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,160
I'm the Thousand-Faced
Eagle King's father.

1448
00:39:49,560 --> 00:39:50,760
How do we get in?

1449
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:52,200
Wait.

1450
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,480
(Ning suddenly remembers)
We have Skill Cards, right?

1451
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,080
Guys.

1452
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:57,080
Wait.

1453
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,800
(Calling God)
"God", list my card slots.

1454
00:39:59,070 --> 00:40:00,960
Please wait. Checking now.

1455
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:01,760
"God",

1456
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,000
can you act a little more like God?

1457
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,280
He's bossing you around like that.

1458
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:05,880
And you're still...

1459
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:06,800
What cards do you have?

1460
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,480
I have the Transport Card.

1461
00:40:10,120 --> 00:40:11,520
Then make something that flies.

1462
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:14,080
Use the Transport Card for a plane.

1463
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:15,440
(Starting to dream big)
Get a plane and fly us up.

1464
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,040
No.

1465
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:16,760
Just use a cannon.

1466
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:17,380
(Sounds fine to me)

1467
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:18,400
Transport?

1468
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,320
We'll ride the cannon later.

1469
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:20,380
(Bro's stumped)

1470
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:21,760
I got it.

1471
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:24,440
(Scheming in progress)
Use the Massage Card right here.

1472
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:26,120
Make them all come give
you a back massage.

1473
00:40:26,260 --> 00:40:28,460
(Not a bad idea)

1474
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:29,920
They'll use their sticks
to really work your back.

1475
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:30,880
(Caring for his little brother)
Exactly.

1476
00:40:31,120 --> 00:40:31,960
Hit my butt.

1477
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:32,660
(Xin is scared)
Exactly.

1478
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,560
Forty whacks for you.

1479
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,320
That works.

1480
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:37,120
But if it's a massage,

1481
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:39,040
how many people can he make do it?

1482
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:39,840
I can only make one person.

1483
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:42,560
I do have two Massage Cards though.

1484
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:44,160
(Chao has a plan)
Just make them massage each other.

1485
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:48,120
(Chao knows how to hit the funny bone)
They massage each other.

1486
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:51,080
(Stop)
What other cards do you have?

1487
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,400
I have a Disguise Card.

1488
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,670
The Disguise Card is easy.

1489
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,840
With the Disguise Card,

1490
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:56,160
I'll just turn into them.

1491
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,040
Exactly.

1492
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,560
I can't walk on stilts, Ning.

1493
00:40:58,560 --> 00:40:59,360
No.

1494
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,560
Turn into the Thousand-Faced Eagle King!

1495
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:01,320
I can't.

1496
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:02,200
Because the Disguise Card

1497
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:03,880
only works if you already know

1498
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:04,560
what they look like.

1499
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:05,480
No problem.

1500
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:06,160
Okay.

1501
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:07,080
Where's my card?

1502
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:10,040
He Ha has an Item Cards,

1503
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:10,920
a Free Card,

1504
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:11,760
a Copy Card,

1505
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:12,560
a Singing Card,

1506
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:13,160
and a Freeze Card.

1507
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,600
You have a Copy Card, right?

1508
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,400
Copy what?

1509
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:19,200
What's a Copy Card for?

1510
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:19,800
No.

1511
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:20,840
Ning, where's your card?

1512
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:21,240
Copy.

1513
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:22,560
I just said freeze and invisible.

1514
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,000
I ran through them quickly.

1515
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,480
I honestly think
only invisible is useful.

1516
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,960
(Ning is confused)
Does invisible mean one person

1517
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:27,600
or all six of us?

1518
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:28,520
One person.

1519
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:30,120
Then what's the point of me going?

1520
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:31,000
It's your solo mission.

1521
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:31,760
Your solo mission.

1522
00:41:31,940 --> 00:41:32,700
(Big brother energy)

1523
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:36,100
Is it group invisibility
or solo invisibility?

1524
00:41:36,100 --> 00:41:38,160
(Checking with "God")
Group or solo invisibility?

1525
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:38,880
Both work.

1526
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,000
Both work.

1527
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:41,720
Fine. Let's do it.

1528
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,440
So after we turn invisible,

1529
00:41:43,440 --> 00:41:44,600
what's the first thing we do?

1530
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:46,200
We take down these four guards first.

1531
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:47,900
(Xin doesn't get it)
But we're already invisible.

1532
00:41:48,180 --> 00:41:49,100
(Totally unnecessary)

1533
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:50,520
Let's knock them out.

1534
00:41:50,520 --> 00:41:51,000
Yeah.

1535
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:52,000
Or why don't we

1536
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:53,160
just knock them out by force?

1537
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:54,100
(Don't forget who we are)
We all know kung fu.

1538
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:55,420
(Insane execution)

1539
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:00,300
(Searching carefully)

1540
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:02,200
I'll give you money.

1541
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:03,240
Can you let us in?

1542
00:42:04,340 --> 00:42:05,140
(Rejected immediately)
No.

1543
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:06,960
Money doesn't work.

1544
00:42:09,350 --> 00:42:10,440
(So cute)
You're so cute.

1545
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:13,200
Pretty noble of you.

1546
00:42:13,220 --> 00:42:15,140
(Casual chatting
after all that brain work)

1547
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,520
Why does your mouth smell so good?

1548
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:18,040
What did you eat?

1549
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:20,840
Why does it smell so good?

1550
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:22,400
(Still beef crisps)
These beef crisps smell so good.

1551
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:24,440
They really smell good.

1552
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:25,240
Are you their spokesperson?

1553
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:26,880
No.

1554
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:29,800
Everyone keeps asking

1555
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:31,040
what these beef crisps are.

1556
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,120
How many years
till the next Year of the Ox?

1557
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:34,560
Rat, ox, tiger, rabbit.

1558
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:36,000
Rat, ox, tiger, rabbit,

1559
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,160
(Already in the DNA)
dragon, snake, horse, goat,

1560
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,240
monkey, rooster, dog, pig.

1561
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:38,840
Ten years, right?

1562
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:39,880
Ten years.

1563
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,040
I'm telling you. The next Ox year

1564
00:42:41,040 --> 00:42:41,560
means waiting

1565
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:42,080
for another zodiac year.

1566
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:43,120
Another zodiac year.

1567
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:45,040
In ten more years?

1568
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,360
(That feels so far away)
Is the Ox year really ten years away?

1569
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,440
Eight years.

1570
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,480
I'll be twenty-eight.

1571
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,560
Twenty-eight?

1572
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:51,600
Yeah, I'll be twenty-eight.

1573
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:53,360
You'll be thirty-six then, right?

1574
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:54,560
Isn't thirty-six the Ox year?

1575
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:54,880
Yeah.

1576
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:55,600
Then when you're thirty-six...

1577
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:58,200
I thought you meant you'd
only be twenty-eight then.

1578
00:42:58,200 --> 00:42:58,640
Thirty-six.

1579
00:42:58,640 --> 00:42:59,520
I really...

1580
00:42:59,520 --> 00:42:59,920
Eight years.

1581
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:01,080
What do you think we'll be like

1582
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:01,920
(Imagining the future)
in eight years?

1583
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:03,240
In nine years, I'll have

1584
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:04,080
another zodiac year.

1585
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:05,240
You'll be thirty-two.

1586
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:06,240
You'll be thirty-two too.

1587
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,800
That's wild,

1588
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:08,800
Ding!

1589
00:43:08,900 --> 00:43:09,400
(The post-00s are shocked)

1590
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,840
In eight years,
I'll already be thirty-two!

1591
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:13,220
(Hard to imagine)
Ding Chengxin and I at thirty-two!

1592
00:43:13,480 --> 00:43:15,480
You'll only be thirty-two
in eight years?

1593
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,980
(The pain of already being there)
I'm already...

1594
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:18,760
(One second ago)
(We'll) only be thirty-two?

1595
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:20,140
(Spoke too soon)
Okay, sorry.

1596
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:22,880
(Loves joking around)
Sorry.

1597
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:25,320
No, Ding.

1598
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:26,980
Do you think we'll
have kids at thirty-two?

1599
00:43:26,980 --> 00:43:27,480
(Curious about the future)

1600
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,600
Like Jin now.

1601
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:30,160
Will we have families and kids?

1602
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:31,880
Not at thirty-two. That's too early.

1603
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:32,680
What about thirty-six?

1604
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:33,880
Do you think you'll have kids then?

1605
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,200
(No rush at all)
I'm not rushing. I'm not rushing at all.

1606
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:35,760
Getting married?

1607
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:36,400
That whole thing

1608
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:39,280
isn't on your schedule before forty.

1609
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:40,960
Who knows what we'll think later?

1610
00:43:40,960 --> 00:43:42,160
(Just going with the flow)
I don't think that way now.

1611
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:42,600
Yeah.

1612
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:44,880
(Still young at heart)
I still feel like a kid.

1613
00:43:44,880 --> 00:43:46,120
Yeah, me too.

1614
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:48,480
(Not grown up yet)
I still feel like a kid too.

1615
00:43:49,700 --> 00:44:31,660
=The Truth Season 4=
(Viewing Calendar)

1616
00:44:48,450 --> 00:44:52,450
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

1617
00:44:52,450 --> 00:44:56,890
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

1618
00:44:58,910 --> 00:45:03,070
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

1619
00:45:03,070 --> 00:45:07,290
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

1620
00:45:07,290 --> 00:45:11,060
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

1621
00:45:11,060 --> 00:45:15,170
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

1622
00:45:15,350 --> 00:45:19,470
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

1623
00:45:19,470 --> 00:45:23,580
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

1624
00:45:23,580 --> 00:45:27,220
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

1625
00:45:27,220 --> 00:45:29,350
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

1626
00:45:29,350 --> 00:45:33,300
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

1627
00:45:33,540 --> 00:45:37,460
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

1628
00:45:37,670 --> 00:45:41,820
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

1629
00:45:41,820 --> 00:45:45,380
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

1630
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:50,290
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
